{
  "stem": "19895.8",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I was 16 at the time when all these things took place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And in another 10, 15 years there will be not too many of us who are alive and well to tell about it, and not many of us who were old enough, like 16, who are alive and well to tell about it.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Because if somebody was four, five years younger, 10 years, eight years old, they-- they lived it through.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The parents were trying to hide them or wherever they survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But they don't have a-- a firsthand information, knowledge of seeing Nazism, hatred at its best.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Because what the Holocaust did for us Jews, is, it has it's, a very, very major segment of darkness in the history of the world.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And I hope and I try to do everything in my life, which literally I can, to speak how much hatred by education should be eliminated.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It is one of the strongest force.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Hatred is easier to spread than love.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And people find every occasion to hate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Many people do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And some people take advantage of that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "There are some leaders who thrive on that and then all kind of horrible things-- ethnic cleansing, Holocausts, and tragedies for humankind can occur, which we would like very much to avoid, and should never, ever happen again.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And if there is anything to learn and-- and-- and testify, it is that this was a time in my life and-- and in the history of humankind which should be a lesson how not to behave to each other, and how not to communicate with each other, and how not to hate each other.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
